\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.8}{\ignorespaces Sequential Pipeline with vs without Early Exit Optimization. (a) Latency comparison showing 1.20$\times $ average latency reduction (65ms $\to $ 54ms) and 2.9$\times $ p50 latency reduction (487ms $\to $ 168ms). Early exit optimization directly reduces average latency by bypassing ML scoring for 3.4\% of Schema-passing records; combined with 10.1\% Schema pre-filtering, 13.5\% of all records avoid the ML scoring stage. (b) Throughput comparison showing 2.2$\times $ improvement (8,240 $\to $ 18,450 events/sec) through early exit and conditional routing.\relax }}{54}{figure.caption.42}}
\newlabel{fig:exp8a_performance}{{5.8}{54}{Sequential Pipeline with vs without Early Exit Optimization. (a) Latency comparison showing 1.20$\times $ average latency reduction (65ms $\to $ 54ms) and 2.9$\times $ p50 latency reduction (487ms $\to $ 168ms). Early exit optimization directly reduces average latency by bypassing ML scoring for 3.4\% of Schema-passing records; combined with 10.1\% Schema pre-filtering, 13.5\% of all records avoid the ML scoring stage. (b) Throughput comparison showing 2.2$\times $ improvement (8,240 $\to $ 18,450 events/sec) through early exit and conditional routing.\relax }{figure.caption.42}{}}
