\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.9}{\ignorespaces FPR Comparison: sklearn IF vs Global Threshold vs 4D Context-Aware Thresholds. The sklearn IF baseline with global threshold (FPR=4.94\%) is the correct apples-to-apples comparison for the thresholding contribution. The 4D context-aware approach reduces FPR to 4.2\% (1.18x improvement). The Global Threshold (FPR=38.7\%) represents a rule-based baseline on raw features and is not a competitive ML baseline.\relax }}{57}{figure.caption.43}}
\newlabel{fig:exp5a_fpr_comparison}{{5.9}{57}{FPR Comparison: sklearn IF vs Global Threshold vs 4D Context-Aware Thresholds. The sklearn IF baseline with global threshold (FPR=4.94\%) is the correct apples-to-apples comparison for the thresholding contribution. The 4D context-aware approach reduces FPR to 4.2\% (1.18x improvement). The Global Threshold (FPR=38.7\%) represents a rule-based baseline on raw features and is not a competitive ML baseline.\relax }{figure.caption.43}{}}
